Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getSdpMode(25.10)                                            getSdpMode(25.10)

Name
       getSdpMode  - Displays the current values of various SDP-related sticky
       options

Syntax
       getSdpMode

       [-help]

       [-clock_location]

       [-disable_extended_core]

       [-honor_dont_use]

       [-honor_orient]

       [-legalization]

       [-legalization_effort]

       [-max_move_distance]

       [-num_column]

       [-place_report]

       [-pre_fixed_cells_blockage_direction]

       [-quiet]

       [-nonDefault]

       Displays the current values of various SDP-related sticky options.  Use
       this  command when you want to retrieve current values of all or speci-
       fied setSdpMode settings. If you do not specify any parameter,  getSdp-
       Mode returns information on all of the setSdpMode parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each getSdpMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man getSdpMode.

       <parameter_names>
              Displays information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters.

              See  setSdpMode for descriptions of the parameters you can spec-
              ify.

       -quiet Displays the current settings for the  specified  parameters  in
              Tcl list format only.

              If  you specify -quiet without any parameters, the software dis-
              plays the current settings of all setSdpMode parameters  in  Tcl
              list format.

       -nonDefault
              Displays the current settings that are not default settings.

Example
              * The  following  command  displays  the  current setting of the
                -clock_location parameter:

                getSdpMode -clock_location

                The software displays the following information:

                -clock_location center # string, default=center

                center

              * The following command displays the current  settings  for  all
                setSdpMode parameters in Tcl list format only:

                getSdpMode -quiet

                The software returns the following information:

                {clock_location     center}    {disable_extended_core    true}
                {honor_dont_use  false}  {honor_orient  false}   {legalization
                NONE}    {legalization_effort   low}   {max_move_distance   0}
                {num_column 2} {place_report {}} {pre_fixed_cells_blockage_di-
                rection NONE}

